task.summary: Finnished modloader and dynamical loading of mods
Further improvement to the mod loading mechanism. Now supporting a mod main file, three init events (PreInit, Init and PostInit) and the ability to specify a modId, mod name and version.
Further improvement to the mod loading mechanism. Now supporting a mod main file, three init events (PreInit, Init and PostInit) and the ability to specify a modId, mod name and version.
Merged changes and removed debugging code
Made a proper world generator for future change. Currently only generates random tiles and no terrain. Furthermore fixed event handling occasionally throwing a ConcurrentModificationException
Moved world package to the correct location
Added entity API and IUpdatable to request updates for any object that needs it
Added smooth camera movement and the delta time in milliseconds between two game ticks to the parameter of the IUpdatable interface
Added TileEntities and click listeners for TileEntities. Map now gets saved as tiles and not as IDs anymore. Like this, data can be stored per block (required for TileEntities to work)
Added proper mouse click functionality to the TileEntity class and added a mod-friendly API for registering, opening and managing GUI Screens
Added method to close the GUI screen again
Fixed some OutOfBounds errors while getting a tile or tile entity from the world
Added mouse and entity related events and started working on an item, GUI and inventory system
Fixed rendering so that all tiles not on screen get clipped. Also made window resizeable
